{"parentUuid": "516afb4f-5a04-4aba-8f42-714f44c92c7e", "isSidechain": false, "message": {"model": "claude-opus-4-6", "id": "msg_012GsFj7kpqxLwqRXgY3NH4P", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "\u00a7 \u25b30.5 \u25ceexpl \u25a0bug \u25c70.7 \u21bb2\n\nYou're right, the first case was a single Write. For that case, the culprit was a **thinking block** \u2014 an invisible assistant JSONL entry between the text and the tool_use:\n\n```\nL_text: assistant text  \u2192  \"All existing... INTENT: Create quota-cache.ts...\"\nL_think: assistant thinking  \u2192  (internal reasoning, no visible text)\nL_tool: assistant tool_use  \u2192  Write(quota-cache.ts)\n```\n\n`_extract_message_parts` produces `{\"text\": \"\", \"tools\": []}` for thinking blocks \u2014 a ghost entry. With n=2, the last 2 assistant entries were `[L_think, L_tool]`. The text entry with INTENT was pushed out by the ghost.\n\nThe fix handles both cases:\n1. **Ghost filtering** \u2014 thinking blocks are now skipped entirely, so for single-file writes the window correctly gets `[L_text, L_tool]`\n2. **Window expansion** \u2014 for parallel writes where multiple tool_use entries push text out"}], "stop_reason": "end_turn", "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 3, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 432, "cache_read_input_tokens": 137863, "output_tokens": 1178, "server_tool_use": {"web_search_requests": 0, "web_fetch_requests": 0}, "service_tier": "standard", "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 432, "ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 0}, "inference_geo": "", "iterations": [{"input_tokens": 3, "output_tokens": 1178, "cache_read_input_tokens": 137863, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 432, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 432}, "type": "message"}], "speed": "standard"}, "diagnostics": null}, "requestId": "req_011CazjAQWzHJ1NWFdHQdRAZ", "type": "assistant", "uuid": "e286a503-fd75-470e-8b20-c64f4